The paper discusses a routing protocol for underwater wireless sensor networks, which involves communication and networking aspects (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the challenges of high error probability and energy consumption, which are related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed protocol involves adaptive mobility of nodes, which falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The paper also discusses weight updating and threshold variation, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper aims to optimize network lifetime, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
